# OctoAcme Project Management Docs

## Overview

This repository centralizes OctoAcmeâ€™s project management processes, making institutional knowledge accessible, versioned, and easily discoverable for all team members. It is part of our initiative to capture, refine, and standardize workflows collaboratively in Copilot Spaces for consistent, repeatable project execution.

OctoAcme uses an iterative, customer-first approach to project management, emphasizing:
- Clear roles and defined deliverables
- Cross-functional collaboration
- Continuous improvement and feedback loops
- Transparent communication and risk management

## Project Management Process Summary

The OctoAcme project management process includes:

- **Initiation:** Defining goals, stakeholders, and success metrics. (See: [Project Initiation Guide](./octoacme-project-initiation.md))
- **Planning:** Creating a roadmap, backlog, and identifying risks. (See: [Project Planning](./octoacme-project-planning.md))
- **Execution & Tracking:** Managing day-to-day work, quality assurance, demos, and reporting. (See: [Execution & Tracking](./octoacme-execution-and-tracking.md))
- **Risk Management & Communication:** Maintaining a risk register, stakeholder updates, and escalation paths. (See: [Risk Management & Communication](./octoacme-risks-and-communication.md))
- **Release & Deployment:** Standardized release types, checklists, and incident response. (See: [Release & Deployment Guide](./octoacme-release-and-deployment.md))
- **Retrospective & Continuous Improvement:** Post-milestone learnings and actionable improvements. (See: [Retrospective & Continuous Improvement](./octoacme-retrospective-and-continuous-improvement.md))
- **Roles & Personas:** Responsibilities for PMs, PdMs, Developers, and typical communication patterns. (See: [Roles & Personas](./octoacme-roles-and-personas.md))

